# Worker Agent Service — Implementation Plan

Build **Layer 8 — Parallel Worker Agent Layer** per architecture blueprint §2.8. Each worker receives one chunk + SQO, extracts citation-bound claims, and returns structured output. Pool manages parallel execution, early stopping, and cost control.

## Proposed Changes

### Worker Schemas

#### [NEW] [schemas.py](file:///c:/HelioX/workers/schemas.py)

Pydantic DTOs matching §2.8 output contract:

| Model | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `SupportingSpan` | `{start, end, text}` — exact quoted span from chunk |
| `WorkerInput` | Input DTO: SQO + single ScoredChunk + token budget |
| `WorkerOutput` | Output DTO: claim, supporting_spans, reasoning_trace, confidence_local, coverage_score, status |
| `WorkerStatus` | Enum: `SUFFICIENT`, `INSUFFICIENT`, `ERROR` |
| `PoolResult` | Aggregated output: all worker outputs, tokens used, early stop flag, timing |
| `TokenUsage` | Per-worker token tracking (input, output, total) |

